# {{PROJECT}} — Workspace Guide for Claude

This is the workspace root for **{{PROJECT}}** ({{PROJECT_DESCRIPTION}}). It contains independent sub-repos. The workspace root is **not** a git repo; each sub-repo is its own repo.

## Repo map

| Repo | Purpose | Stack |
|---|---|---|
| `{{PROJECT}}-core/` | Primary backend — REST API, business logic | {{BACKEND_RUNTIME}} + {{DB}}{{#CACHE}} + {{CACHE}}{{/CACHE}} |
{{#MOBILE}}| `{{PROJECT}}-app/` | Mobile app | {{MOBILE}} |
{{/MOBILE}}{{#WEB}}| `{{PROJECT}}-web/` | Public web app | {{WEB}} |
{{/WEB}}{{#WEB_ADMIN}}| `{{PROJECT}}-web-admin/` | Admin console | Next.js |
{{/WEB_ADMIN}}{{#E2E_GATE}}| `{{PROJECT}}-app-tests/` | Mobile E2E (Appium + WebdriverIO + Mocha) | Node + Appium |
{{/E2E_GATE}}| `{{PROJECT}}-deployment/` | Docker Compose, nginx, env templates | Docker + nginx |

Shared, **read-only** service this workspace depends on:

- `{{USER_SERVICE_PATH}}` — `user-service` (image `{{USER_SERVICE_IMAGE}}`). Handles user management, email delivery, and asset/image hosting. Never edit from this workspace.

## Planned future services

These responsibilities live inside `user-service` today and will split into independent services later. Designs should keep these boundaries clean so the future split is mechanical:

- `email-service` — transactional + marketing email
- `asset-service` — user-uploaded images, public assets
- `notification-service` — push, in-app, webhook fan-out

When wiring new code, call these via a thin internal client, not by reaching into `user-service` internals.

## Service topology

```
                          ┌──────────────┐
            ┌────────────►│ user-service │
            │             └──────────────┘
            │
client ──► nginx ──► {{PROJECT}}-core ──► {{DB}}{{#CACHE}}
                          │              {{CACHE}}{{/CACHE}}
                          └─► swagger-ui
```

- nginx routes (defined in `{{PROJECT}}-deployment/shared/nginx/locations.conf`, shared across all envs):
  - `{{API_BASE}}/auth`, `{{API_BASE}}/users`, `{{API_BASE}}/email`, `{{API_BASE}}/assets` → `user-service`
  - `{{API_BASE}}/*` (catch-all) → `{{PROJECT}}-core`
  - `/api-docs/*` → `swagger-ui`
- The `{{API_VERSION_HEADER}}` header is forwarded unchanged via `proxy_pass_header`.

## API contract (summary)

- Base path: `{{API_BASE}}` (no URL versioning)
- Version header: `{{API_VERSION_HEADER}}: {{API_VERSION_DEFAULT}}` (required on every request to versioned routes)
- Success body: the resource itself, no envelope. Lists: `{ "items": [...], "nextCursor": "...", "hasMore": true, "limit": 20 }`.
- Error body (flat, no wrapper): `{ "code": "SCREAMING_SNAKE", "message": "...", "details"?: {...}, "requestId"?: "..." }`
- HTTP status is the source of truth for success vs error. No `success` boolean in the body.
- Auth: Bearer JWT from `user-service`. `{{PROJECT}}-core` only validates — never issues.

Full contract: `docs/API_CONTRACT.md`. Coding conventions: `docs/CODING_PRACTICES.md`.

