## Branch model

`main ← dev ← <issue-id>_<snake_slug>`

- PRs always target `dev`. Merge to `main` is manual, post-review.
- Direct push to `main` is blocked by `.claude/hooks/block-main-pushes.ps1`.
- Branch naming: `<issue-id>_<snake_slug>` (Mode A) or `<snake_slug>` (Mode B). Lowercase ASCII, `_`-joined, ≤5 words.{{#HOTFIX}}
- Hotfix: `/hotfix <message>` pushes directly to `dev` after local gate. Logged to `HOTFIX_LOG.md`. **Never** touches `main`.{{/HOTFIX}}

## Sub-agent delegation rules

Each `*-specialist` agent is scoped to one repo and **must not** read or modify files outside its repo. Delegate via the `Agent` tool with the matching `subagent_type`:

| Repo | Agent |
|---|---|
| `{{PROJECT}}-core/` | `backend-specialist` |
{{#MOBILE}}| `{{PROJECT}}-app/` | `mobile-specialist` |
{{/MOBILE}}{{#WEB}}| `{{PROJECT}}-web/` | `web-specialist` |
{{/WEB}}{{#WEB_ADMIN}}| `{{PROJECT}}-web-admin/` | `web-admin-specialist` |
{{/WEB_ADMIN}}| `{{PROJECT}}-deployment/` | `deployment-specialist` |
{{#E2E_GATE}}| `{{PROJECT}}-app-tests/` | `test-specialist` |
{{/E2E_GATE}}

Order of operations when a change spans repos: contracts first (`backend-specialist`), then clients (`mobile-specialist` / `web-specialist`) in parallel. Tests after the contracts settle.

## Workflow commands

- `/run-issue <id-or-prompt>` — Phases 0–8 of `WORKFLOW.md`. Stops at draft PR.
{{#E2E_GATE}}- `/run-e2e <id-or-branch>` — Appium loop. Marks PR ready-for-review on pass.
- `/ship-issue <id-or-prompt>` — chains `/run-issue` then `/run-e2e`.
{{/E2E_GATE}}{{#HOTFIX}}- `/hotfix <message>` — local gate → push to `dev`. Never `main`.
{{/HOTFIX}}

Full lifecycle: `WORKFLOW.md`.

